&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buy the model &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.es/dp/B07FNTMWMT?tag=redken-21"&gt;Lego 75894 - 1967 Mini Cooper S Rally and 2018 Mini John Cooper Works Buggy&amp;nbsp;🛒&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buy the instructions at the &lt;span class="caps"&gt;MOC&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="caps"&gt;URL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After several times trying to pay for the instructions (which I was unable to get because
PayPal complained on the web site), I decided to make my own based on what I could see, and the result, are the images you can see, the initial model which had a small driving area and no minifig could sit there and the final one which added some more options like sizing cabin for allowing a minifigure to &lt;code&gt;drive&lt;/code&gt;, plus some other alternatives for the front facing engine area and better holding of the rear wheels&amp;nbsp;area.&lt;/p&gt;
